<p><strong>Question 1:</strong> What is social psychology?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Social psychology is the scientific study of how individuals think, feel, and behave in social situations. It examines the influence of both social and environmental factors on our thoughts, emotions, and actions.</p>
<p><strong>Question 2:</strong> What are the key concepts in social psychology?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Some of the key concepts in social psychology include: schemas, attitudes, social influence, conformity, obedience, and aggression. Schemas are mental frameworks we use to organize information and understand the social world. Attitudes are our beliefs and feelings about people, objects, or ideas. Social influence refers to the ways in which others influence our thoughts, feelings, and behaviors. Conformity is the tendency to change our behavior in order to fit in with others. Obedience is the tendency to follow the orders of an authority figure. Aggression is any behavior that aims to cause physical or psychological harm to others.</p>
<p><strong>Question 3:</strong> What are the major theories of social psychology?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> There are several major theories of social psychology, including: the social identity theory, the social exchange theory, the attribution theory, and the evolutionary psychology theory. The social identity theory focuses on how our self-concept is shaped by our social group affiliations. The social exchange theory explains social behavior in terms of rewards and costs. The attribution theory examines how we attribute causes to our own behavior and the behavior of others. The evolutionary psychology theory argues that many of our social behaviors are shaped by our evolutionary history.</p>
<p><strong>Question 4:</strong> What are the implications of social psychology for our daily lives?</p>
<p><strong>Answer:</strong> Social psychology has important implications for our daily lives. It can help us to understand how to communicate effectively, build strong relationships, and make better decisions. It can also help us to be more aware of the ways in which we are influenced by others and to resist negative social influences.</p>
